2009-07-24  Guillaume-Jean Herbiet <Guillaume.Herbiet@uni.lu>

	* [r36] bin/backup.in: Fixed bug with sparsebundle target: default
	  mountpoint "Backup_Sparsebundle" was used which caused creation
	  of simlink "latest" that was broken when mounting the
	  sparsebundle manually if the sparsebundle name differed from
	  "Backup_Sparsebundle".

	* [r35] bin/backup.in: Experimental implementation of backup
	  history :
	  - Each backup creates a timestamped directory in the specified
	  target where files are backuped. To limit disk usage, unchanged
	  files are hard linked with existing version on target.
	  - Up-to-date snapshot is always available under the "latest"
	  directory.
	  - (Not yet supported) Backup with history over SSH, causes a
	  backup failure
	  - (Not yet implemented) Behavior on target disk full
	  - (Not yet implemented) History consolidation
	  - (Not yet implemented) Retrieve mode from latest snapshot,
	  causes a retrieve failure

	* [r34] TODO, bin/backup.in: - Modified sparsebundle protocol error
	  messages to be more consistant with other protocols
	  - Updated TODO to reflect recent modifications

2009-07-23  Guillaume-Jean Herbiet <Guillaume.Herbiet@uni.lu>

	* [r33] INSTALL, bin/backup.in: - Added support for rsync with Mac
	  OS resource forks (extended attributes), see -m option
	  - Added support for pre/post backup scripts, see --pre-backup and
	  --post-backup options
	  - Added support for sparsebundle images through the
	  sparsebundle:/// protocol
	  - Added user notification (Growl under Mac OS X, notify-send
	  under Linux), see the --notification option
	  
	  POD documentation is updated accordingly.

